One Concern
The repeatedness dimension is smart but hard to score in Phase 2. When Claude sees a batch of 10 dates, it doesn't have context about whether the same story appeared on previous dates. It can only judge within the same day's articles. This means cross-day repeatedness (Monday's OpenAI story rehashed on Tuesday) won't be captured. This is acceptable — within-day dedup is the main value, and the prediction model will naturally handle multi-day decay through lagged features.



Plan: Academic Model Research and Comparison for Stage 3 (News-Enhanced Prediction)
Context
The project has completed Stage 1 (news impact scoring via event study methodology) and Stage 2 (price-only baseline with Ridge/LightGBM, best R2_OOS=5.6%). The key finding from Entry 26 is that price-only models shrink predictions to ~20% of actual variance, with a tail/core MAE ratio of 4.8x — extreme days driven by news are fundamentally unpredictable from price alone.

The user requests: research academically validated models from GitHub papers that combine price + news for stock prediction, find the most robust, and compare methodology to our current approach. Updated with 2024-2025 state-of-the-art.

The 2024-2025 Paradigm Shift
The field has moved significantly since 2022. Key changes:

FinBERT (2019) is no longer SOTA. Llama-3-70B achieves 79.3% on financial sentiment vs FinBERT's 59.7%. FinLlama (Llama-2 fine-tuned) produced 44.7% higher cumulative returns than FinBERT in trading tests.

LLMs as feature extractors, not predictors. The major insight from 2024-2025: LLMs are terrible at directly predicting prices (worse than linear regression), but excellent at extracting structured features (event type, severity, duration, affected entities). This is a paradigm shift from "embed and predict" to "extract and predict."

Gated cross-attention beats simple concatenation. MSGCA (2024) achieves 8-32% improvement over previous SOTA by learning to dynamically weight modalities. When news is contradictory, the model downweights it; when price signal is strong, it upweights price.

LLM embeddings outperform FinBERT. Guo & Hauptmann (EMNLP 2024) showed token-level LLM embeddings produce stronger portfolios than conventional sentiment scores or FinBERT embeddings.

Chain-of-Thought reasoning for finance. Fino1 (Feb 2025) with CoT + RL outperforms GPT-o1, DeepSeek-R1, and GPT-4.5 on financial reasoning tasks.

Reality check: improvements are modest. Even SOTA achieves ~60-65% directional accuracy. LLM-based trading strategy Sharpe ratios are declining (6.54 in 2021 → 1.22 in 2024) as markets adapt. Simple methods remain competitive.

