Detailed Comparison to Our Methodology
Ke, Kelly, Xiu (2019) — Most Philosophically Aligned
Similar: Both target market model residuals. Both use Ridge/LASSO. Both pool across stocks. Infeasible for us: Requires millions of articles for word-level weight learning. Our 4,440 articles is 100x too small. Extractable insight: Sentiment should be adapted to predict returns, not just classify tone.

Duan et al. (2018) — Best Target Match (CAR)
Similar: Both predict Cumulative Abnormal Returns (our cum3d_excess). Headline+summary maps to their abstract+document. Infeasible for us: Attention model millions of parameters → overfit on 4,440 articles. Extractable insight: Target cum3d, use headline as guiding signal for embeddings.

PEAD.txt (2021) — Foundation of Our Approach
Similar: Frozen embeddings into ML models for multi-day drift prediction. Why it fits: No fine-tuning needed, compatible with Ridge/LightGBM, targets multi-day drift. Limitation: Uses Sentence-BERT (2019) — newer LLM embeddings outperform it.

Guo & Hauptmann (EMNLP 2024) — Updated Embedding Approach
Key finding: Token-level LLM embeddings outperform conventional sentiment scores AND FinBERT for stock return prediction. Decoder-based LLMs (GPT-style) produce stronger features than encoder-based (BERT-style). Relevance: This is the 2024 update to the PEAD.txt approach — same architecture (frozen encoder → features → ML), but with a better encoder. Practical constraint: Large LLM inference is expensive. Need to balance quality vs compute.

MSGCA (2024) — Best Fusion Architecture
Key finding: Gated cross-attention between price + text + graph modalities, with learned gates that dynamically weight contributions. 8-32% improvement over simple concatenation. Relevance: Our late-fusion plan (concatenate features) may leave performance on the table. Gated fusion could help when news is contradictory or missing. Practical constraint: Requires neural network training. May overfit on our small dataset.

Fino1 (Feb 2025) — Best Financial Reasoning
Key finding: CoT + RL on Llama-3.1-8B outperforms GPT-o1 and GPT-4.5 on financial reasoning. Relevance: Could be used for structured feature extraction (event type, severity, duration) rather than just embeddings. Practical constraint: Requires API calls or local GPU for 8B model inference.

AlphaFin (2024) — RAG Approach
Key finding: RAG + Stock-Chain contextualizes news with historical patterns. 30%+ ARR. Relevance: Could ground news impact prediction in historical event similarity. Practical constraint: Complex infrastructure. Best reserved as a stretch goal.

NLP Model Decision: Updated for 2024-2025
Performance Hierarchy (2024-2025 evidence)
Model	Financial Sentiment Accuracy	Return Prediction Quality	Compute Cost	Availability
Llama-3-70B	79.3%	Best (decoder LLM embeddings)	High (70B params)	Open-source
Fino1 (8B)	—	Best reasoning	Medium (8B params)	Open-source
