GPT-4o	68.2%	Comparable to stat models	API cost	Proprietary
Recommended Approach: Two-Track Strategy
Given our constraints (4,440 articles, 7 stocks, academic rigor, reproducibility), the updated recommendation is:

Track A (Primary): Frozen LLM Embeddings — Modernized PEAD-Lite

Use a modern encoder instead of FinBERT. Options in order of preference:
Sentence-Transformers all-MiniLM-L6-v2 or all-mpnet-base-v2 (384/768 dims, fast, CPU-friendly, better than original S-BERT)
FinBERT as comparison baseline (to measure the improvement from modern encoders)
Llama-3-8B embeddings (if GPU available — extract hidden state as embedding)
Late fusion into Ridge/LightGBM (same as before)
This is the minimal viable approach — fast, reproducible, ablatable
Track B (Enhanced): LLM-Structured Feature Extraction — The 2024-2025 Innovation

Use an LLM (GPT-4o or Claude API, or local Fino1/Llama) to extract structured features from each article:
event_type: earnings, product_launch, regulatory, M&A, analyst_rating, macro, legal, leadership, other
severity: 1-5 scale (how significant is this event?)
expected_duration: transient (1 day), short (2-5 days), persistent (weeks+)
direction_signal: positive, negative, mixed, neutral
specificity: company-specific, sector-wide, market-wide
These become categorical/ordinal features alongside embeddings
This is the paradigm shift: structured extraction >> raw embeddings for interpretability and signal quality
With only 4,440 articles, LLM API cost is trivial (~$5-15 for GPT-4o)
Track C (Stretch): Gated Fusion

If Track A/B show signal, test MSGCA-style gated fusion between price and news modalities
Only worth trying if simple concatenation underperforms expectations
Updated Implementation Plan
Phase 1: Embedding Extraction (Two Encoders)
New file: src/news_embeddings.py

Extract embeddings from BOTH:
sentence-transformers/all-mpnet-base-v2 (768-dim, modern S-BERT, CPU-friendly)
ProsusAI/finbert (768-dim, for comparison)
Input: headline + " " + summary from news.csv
Output: data/output/news_embeddings_mpnet.csv and news_embeddings_finbert.csv
Also extract FinBERT sentiment probabilities (pos/neg/neu)
~8 min total on CPU (4,440 articles × 2 models)
Add sentence-transformers>=2.2, transformers>=4.30, torch>=2.0 to requirements.txt
Phase 2: LLM Structured Feature Extraction (Track B)
New file: src/news_llm_features.py

For each of the 4,440 articles, call an LLM (Claude API or GPT-4o) with a structured prompt:
Given this financial news headline and summary about {ticker}:
Headline: {headline}
Summary: {summary}

Extract:
1. event_type: [earnings|product|regulatory|M&A|analyst|macro|legal|leadership|other]
2. severity: [1-5, where 5 = most market-moving]
3. expected_duration: [transient|short|persistent]
4. direction_signal: [positive|negative|mixed|neutral]
5. specificity: [company|sector|market]

Return JSON only.
Output: data/output/news_structured_features.csv
Cost: ~$5-15 for 4,440 articles via API
This is the 2024-2025 innovation: structured LLM features, not just embeddings
Phase 3: Day-Level Feature Aggregation
New file: src/news_features.py

Aggregate article-level features to (ticker, date) using score_pipeline.py's gap/cc bucketing
For embeddings: max-pool when multiple articles; zero vector when none
For structured features: take the max severity article's features (or aggregate)
PCA on embeddings (fit on training window only)
Binary has_news_gap, has_news_cc indicators
Save data/output/day_news_features.csv
Phase 4: News-Enhanced Model
New file: src/model_news.py (extends model_baseline.py)

Feature set options (tested as ablations):
A: 41 price + PCA embeddings (mpnet) + has_news = ~93 features
B: 41 price + 3 FinBERT sentiment + has_news = ~45 features
C: 41 price + LLM structured features (one-hot event_type + severity + duration + direction + specificity) + has_news = ~60 features
D: 41 price + PCA embeddings + LLM structured = ~110 features (full model)
Same walk-forward, embargo, monthly refit, Clark-West evaluation
PCA fit inside walk-forward loop
Phase 5: Ablation Experiments
Each as a separate journal entry with pre-committed criteria:

Experiment	What It Tests	Success Criterion
3A: mpnet vs FinBERT embeddings	Does modern encoder help?	mpnet R2_OOS > FinBERT R2_OOS by >1pp
3B: Embeddings vs sentiment vs structured	Which feature type wins?	Compare R2_OOS across A/B/C/D
3C: PCA dimensionality	Optimal embedding compression	Choose N maximizing R2_OOS on cc_excess
3D: Tail-focused evaluation	Does news help extreme days?	Tail/core MAE ratio < 3.5x
3E: Same-day gap news	Pre-market news for gap?	Gap R2_OOS improves by >1pp
Phase 6 (Stretch): Advanced Architectures
Only if Phase 5 shows signal
6A: Gated fusion (MSGCA-style learned modality weights)
6B: LSTM on 5-day embedding sequences
6C: Cross-stock features (max A_cc across other 6 tickers)
6D: RAG-based historical event matching (AlphaFin-style)
Pre-Committed Success Criteria
Primary: cc_excess R2_OOS > 5.6% (CW p<0.05) OR cum3d_excess R2_OOS > 2.9% (CW p<0.005)
Secondary: Tail/core MAE ratio drops from 4.8x to below 3.5x on any target
Guard rail: Core MAE (80% normal days) must not degrade by >5% vs baseline
Key Architectural Decisions (Updated 2024-2025)
Decision	Choice	2024-2025 Evidence
Encoder model	all-mpnet-base-v2 (primary) + FinBERT (comparison)	Modern S-BERT encoders outperform FinBERT; Llama-3-70B is best but too heavy for CPU
Structured extraction	LLM API (Claude/GPT-4o) for event_type, severity, duration	2024-2025 paradigm: LLMs as feature extractors >> LLMs as predictors. Trivial cost for 4,440 articles
Fusion strategy	Late fusion first, gated fusion as stretch	MSGCA shows 8-32% gain from gated fusion, but needs neural net training → risky on small data
Dimensionality	PCA to 50 (test 10-100)	Same as before — 768 dims needs reduction for LightGBM
Multi-article days	Max-pool embeddings	Same — captures strongest signal
No-news days	Zero vector + has_news binary	Same — natural sparsity
Primary target	cum3d_excess	Confirmed by PEAD.txt, Duan et al., and our Entry 25
Feature timing	Lag all news by 1 day (same-day gap experiment separately)	Same
Risk Assessment
Risk	Mitigation
4,440 articles is thin	Frozen encoder (no fine-tuning), has_news gate, Ridge shrinkage
Modern encoder not finance-specific	Test FinBERT alongside; 768 dims encode topic beyond sentiment
LLM structured extraction inconsistent	Validate on 50-article sample first; use strict JSON schema
Overfitting with ~110 features	Walk-forward embargo, Ridge L2, LightGBM regularization, PCA
210-prediction test too small for significance	Use cum3d (stronger signal), report effect sizes alongside p-values
Gated fusion overfits on small data	Only attempt as stretch after confirming signal from late fusion
